\begin{align} &\rho \sim \text{Norm}(1.050, 0.2296) \\[1em] &V \sim \text{Norm}(\mu_V, \sigma_V) \\[1em] &m \sim \text{Norm}(\rho V, \sigma_m) \\[1em] &\ell \sim \text{Norm}(a V^{1/3}, \sigma_\ell) \end{align}

[1]:

import numpy as np

import bokeh.io
import bokeh.plotting
bokeh.io.output_notebook()
Loading BokehJS ... 
[19]:

rng = np.random.default_rng()
n = 50000
mu_V = 1
sigma_V = 0.1
rho = 1
a = 1
sigma_m = 0.001
sigma_l = 0.001
V = rng.normal(mu_V, sigma_V, size=n)
m = rng.normal(rho * V, sigma_m)
ell = rng.normal(a * np.cbrt(V), sigma_l)

[20]:

p = bokeh.plotting.figure(
    frame_width=200,
    frame_height=200,
    x_axis_label='mass (JB units)',
    y_axis_label='length (JB units of length)',
)

p.scatter(m, ell, size=2, alpha=0.3)

bokeh.io.show(p)
